This Privacy Policy explains the following to visitors and users of our Services:
– the way we collect personal data and why we do so;
– how we use your personal data;
– how we safeguard your personal data;
– how we disclose your personal data, and
– the choices you have about your personal data.
The Privacy Policy applies only to the Services. If you choose to use our Services, then you agree to the
collection and use of information in relation to this Privacy Policy. The Personal Information (as defined
elsewhere in this Privacy Policy) that we collect is used for providing and improving the Services. We will
not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy. Our Terms of
Service (“Terms”) govern all use of our Services and together with the Privacy Policy constitutes your
agreement with us (“Agreements”).
2. AMENDMENTS TO POLICY
We keep our Privacy Policy under regular review. We will notify any changes made to the Privacy Policy
on the Website and the App Service, by posting a notice in the Services’ News area before the date on
which such changes become effective. Therefore, you are advised to review the Services’ News
periodically.
Once the amended Privacy Policy is posted on the Terms of Service area in the Services, it has taken
effect. Your continued use of the Services after the effective date will be subject to the new Privacy
Policy.
It is important that any data we hold for you is accurate and current. Please keep us informed if your
personal data changes during our relationship with you.
3. INFORMATION COLLECTION AND USE
To ensure that you have the best experience while using our Services, we may require you to provide us
with certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to username, country of
residence, and uploaded images (the “Personal Information”). It does not cover information which cannot
be used to identify you. The Personal Information that we request will be retained by us and used as
described in this Privacy Policy.
4. MINORS
Services are intended only for access and use by individuals of at least 13 years of age. Therefore, we
do not knowingly collect or solicit Personal Information about or direct or target interest-based advertising
to anyone who is under the age of 13 or is otherwise considered to be a minor according to the
applicable laws (a “Minor”), or knowingly allow such persons to have access to or use the Services. If
you are a Minor, please do not send any Personal Information about yourself to us, including your user
name or country of residence. No one who is a Minor may provide any Personal Information. If you
become aware that a Minor has provided us with their Personal Information, please contact us. If we
become aware that we have collected Personal Information from a Minor without verification of parental
consent, we will immediately take steps to remove that information from our servers.
