7.6
to detect, prevent and address technical issues;
7.7
to fulfill any other purpose for which you provide it;
7.8
to carry out our obligations and enforce our rights arising from any contracts entered into
between you and us, including for billing and collection;
7.9
to provide you with notices about your user account, email-instructions, updates etc.;
7.10
to provide you with news, special offers and general information about other goods, services and
events which we offer that are similar to those that you have already enquired about unless you
have opted not to receive such information;
7.11
in any other way we may describe when you provide the information;
7.12
for any other purpose with your consent.
8. HOW WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION SAFE
We protect your information in many different ways. These includes staff training, investing in technology
and following strict handling and storing procedures. We maintain appropriate organisational and
technological safeguards to help protect against loss, misuse or unauthorised access, disclosure,
alteration, or destruction of the information we hold about you. We also seek to ensure that our Service
Providers do the same. Unfortunately, no system can be guaranteed as completely secure and there is
an inherent risk in transmitting information over the internet. It may be possible for an unrelated party to
intercept or access such transmissions unlawfully. If you believe that your personal information under our
control has been compromised, including access to your User account, please contact us immediately at
the following:
vandaleak.official@gmail.com
9. HOW LONG WILL WE KEEP YOUR INFORMATION
We keep your Personal Information for as long as we need to provide the Services to you and fulfill
the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. When your User account is deleted your information is too.
When we delete your Personal Information and there is no need for us to keep it to comply with our legal
or regulatory obligations, we will remove it from our systems. When removing your Personal Information,
we will take commercially reasonable and technically feasible measures to make said Personal
Information irrecoverable and irreproducible.
10. WHO CAN SEE YOUR DATA
To combat fraud, spamming, phishing and other fraudulent or criminal acts we may disclose Personal
Information that we collect, or you provide:
10.1 Disclosure for Law Enforcement.
Under certain circumstances, we may be required to disclose your Personal Information if required to do
so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities.
10.2 Business Transaction.
If we or our subsidiaries are involved in a merger, acquisition or asset sale, your Personal Information
may be transferred.
10.3 Other cases.
We may disclose your information also:
– to our subsidiaries and affiliates;
– to contractors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our business, and
if we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of Biokip, our
customers, or others.
